G.F., New spectrophotometric equations for determining chlorophylls a, b, c1 and c2 in higher plants, algae and natura phytoplankton (1975) Biochem. Physiol. Pflanz., 167, pp. 191-194; Dubois, M., Giles, K.A., Hamilton, J.K., Rebers, P.A., Smith, F., Colorimetric method for determination of sugar and related substances (1956) Anal. Chem., 28, pp. 350-356; Smith, P.K., Measurement of protein using bicinchoninic acid (1985) Anal. Biochem., 150, pp. 76-85; (1999) SAS/STAT Software Version 8.02, , SAS Institute, Cary, North Carolina; Palardy, J.E., Grottoli, A.G., Matthews, K.A., Effects of upwelling, depth, morphology and polyp size on feeding in three species of Panamanian corals (2005) Mar. Ecol. Prog. Ser., 300, pp. 79-89; Palardy, J.E., Grottoli, A.G., Matthews, K.A., Effect of naturally changing zooplankton concentrations on feeding rates of two coral species in the Eastern Pacific (2006) J. Exp. Mar. Biol. Ecol., 331, pp. 99-107; Heidelberg, K.B., Sebens, K.P., Purcell, J.E., Composition and sources of near reef zooplankton on a Jamaican forereef along with implications for cora feeding (2004) Coral Reefs, 23, pp. 263-280; Houlbrèque, F., Tambutté, E., Richard, C., Ferrier-Pagès, C., Importance of a micro-diet for scleractinian corals (2004) Mar. Ecol. Prog. Ser., 282, pp. 151-160","Grottoli, A.G.; Department of Geological Sciences, Ohio State University, Columbus, OH 43210, United States; email: grottoli.1@osu.edu",,,"Nature Publishing Group",,,,,00280836,,NATUA,16641995,"English","Nature",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-33646382859
